SUMMARY:Bug | Transfixed: Michael Shannon on Screen\, Jorgensen Guest Fil
 mmaker Series
DESCRIPTION:Michael Shannon and Ashley Judd give searing performances in 
 this skin-crawling exercise in fear and paranoia from director William Fr
 iedkin. Oklahoma waitress Aggie (Judd) lives a largely solitary life in a
  rundown motel. She's haunted by a tragic past and hounded by her ex-con 
 ex-husband (Harry Connick\, Jr.). When she sparks a romance with an eccen
 tric drifter\, Peter Evans (Shannon)\, she starts to feel hopeful againâ€
 ”until Peter reveals he is a victim of government experimentation. The co
 uple begins to obsess over the nightmarish idea that they are infected by
  insects. Shannon reprises the role he originated in playwright Tracy Let
 ts' original London production of the same name. [102 min\; drama\, thril
 ler\, horror\; English]
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  Michael Shannon and Ashley Judd give se
 aring performances in this skin-crawling exercise in fear and paranoia fr
 om director William Friedkin. Oklahoma waitress Aggie (Judd) lives a larg
 ely solitary life in a rundown motel. She's haunted by a tragic past and 
 hounded by her ex-con ex-husband (Harry Connick\, Jr.). When she sparks a
  romance with an eccentric drifter\, Peter Evans (Shannon)\, she starts t
 o feel hopeful againâ€”until Peter reveals he is a victim of government e
 xperimentation. The couple begins to obsess over the nightmarish idea tha
 t they are infected by insects. Shannon reprises the role he originated i
 n playwright Tracy Letts' original London production of the same name. [1
 02 min\; drama\, thriller\, horror\; English]</p>
