SUMMARY:Crash (1996) | Additional Films and Guests
DESCRIPTION:Based on the equally infamous J.G. Ballard novel\, David Cron
 enberg's 1996 film Crash is built to rattle cultural cages\, spark heated
  debated and discussion\, and draw you into a cinematic world like no oth
 er. Aestheticizing the erotic allure of auto collisions and prodding at t
 he human fascination with death and danger\, Cronenberg crafts a utterly 
 singular film thatâ€”at the time of its releaseâ€”addressed head-on the s
 ocial fears of the swiftly approaching millennium. 30 years later\, the f
 ilm takes an a different\, but still immediate\, resonance in a world liv
 ing through one "unprecedented" event after another. [100 min\; drama\, t
 hriller\; English]
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  Based on the equally infamous J.G. Ball
 ard novel\, David Cronenberg's 1996 film <i>Crash</i> is built to rattle 
 cultural cages\, spark heated debated and discussion\, and draw you into 
 a cinematic world like no other. Aestheticizing the erotic allure of auto
  collisions and prodding at the human fascination with death and danger\,
  Cronenberg crafts a utterly singular film thatâ€”at the time of its rele
 aseâ€”addressed head-on the social fears of the swiftly approaching mille
 nnium. 30 years later\, the film takes an a different\, but still immedia
 te\, resonance in a world living through one "unprecedented" event after 
 another. [100 min\; drama\, thriller\; English]</p>
